Ford’s Turkey Unit Increases 2011 Sales Forecast 2% in July

-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 
2011-07-11T07:18:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-11/ford-s-turkey-unit-increases-2011-sales-forecast-2-in-july.html
Ford Otomotiv Sanayi AS (FROTO) , a joint
venture between Ford Motor Co. and Turkey’s  Koc Holding AS (KCHOL) ,
today increased its estimates for 2011 sales to 351,000 units
in July from 345,000 forecast a month ago.  The revised forecast represents a 16 percent rise over the
sales in 2010, Ford Otosan, as the carmaker is known, said on
its  website .  Kocaeli, Turkey-based Ford Otosan forecast exports of
216,000 units for 2011, up from 214,000 predicted in June and
compared to 177,000 in 2010. Domestic sales may reach 135,000
units, compared with 131,000 in the previous estimate and
126,000 in 2010.  The company expects to produce 292,000 units this year with
an increase of 21 percent from 2010’s 242,000. It said it aims
to invest $300 million this year, compared to $56 million a year
ago.  Turkey ’s total vehicle market, including trucks will be
882,000 this year, an increase of 11 percent from 792,000 in
2010, the company said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
 bkammel@bloomberg.net . 